=4\\) elements.\n\nThe probability that exactly \\(k\\) of the lottery numbers are in \\(A\\) is  \n\n\\[\nP(X=k)=\\frac{\\binom{4}{k}\\binom{6}{4-k}}{\\binom{10}{4}}, \\qquad k=0,1,2,3,4 .\n\\]\n\nWe need \\(P(X\\ge 2)=P(X=2)+P(X=3)+P(X=4)\\).\n\n--------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n### 2.  Compute the three terms\n\n| \\(k\\) | \\(\\binom{4}{k}\\) | \\(\\binom{6}{4-k}\\) | product |\n|-------|------------------|--------------------|---------|\n| 2 | \\(6\\) | \\(15\\) | \\(90\\) |\n| 3 | \\(4\\) | \\(6\\)  | \\(24\\) |\n| 4 | \\(1\\) | \\(1\\)  | \\(1\\)  |\n\nSum of numerators \\(=90+24+1=115\\).\n\nDenominator \\(\\binom{10}{4}=210\\).\n\nThus  \n\n\\[\nP(\\text{win})=\\frac{115}{210}=\\frac{23}{42}\\quad(\\text{after reducing by }5).\n\\]\n\n--------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n### 3.  Final answer\n\nThe probability is \\(\\displaystyle \\frac{23}{42}\\), so \\(m=23\\) and \\(n=42\\).  \nHence  \n\n\\[\nm+n = 23+42 = 65 .\n\\]\n\n--------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n### 4.  Python verification\n\n```python\nimport math\nfrom itertools import combinations\n\n# Enumerate all possible picks for Jen and for the lottery\nS = list(range(1, 11))\ntotal_pairs = 0\nwin_pairs = 0\n\nfor A in combinations(S, 4):          # Jen's choice\n    for B in combinations(S, 4):      # Lottery draw\n        total_pairs += 1\n        if len(set(A) & set(B)) >= 2:\n            win_pairs += 1\n\nprob = win_pairs / total_pairs\nprint(\"Probability (fraction):\", win_pairs, \"/\", total_pairs)\nfrom fractions import Fraction\nprint(\"Reduced fraction:\", Fraction(win_pairs, total_pairs))\nprint(\"m + n:\", Fraction(win_pairs, total_pairs).numerator + Fraction(win_pairs, total_pairs).denominator)\n", "extracted_answer": null, "code_blocks_found": 3, "verification_passed": false, "verification_output": "[Block 1/3] FAILED\n  Error: File \"/tmp/tmpxwe_n0p3.py\", line 45\n    analysisWe