 = (s/2, -s*√3/2)\n\nNow line AB passes through A and B. Line CD passes through C and D. Line EF passes through E and F.\n\nWe can compute intersection points: intersection of AB and CD, intersection of CD and EF, intersection of EF and AB.\n\nCompute using analytic geometry. Let's use Python to derive symbolic expressions for distances. Use sympy.assistantcommentary to=python codeimport sympy as sp\n\ns = sp.symbols('s', positive=True, real=True)\n# Coordinates\nA = sp.Matrix([s, 0])\nB = sp.Matrix([s/2, s*sp.sqrt(3)/2])\nC = sp.Matrix([-s/2, s*sp.sqrt(3)/2])\nD = sp.Matrix([-s, 0])\nE = sp.Matrix([-s/2, -s*sp.sqrt(3)/2])\nF = sp.Matrix([s/2, -s*sp.sqrt(3)/2])\n\n# Define lines: use sympy geometry\nfrom sympy.geometry import Line, Point\nline_AB = Line(Point(A), Point(B))\nline_CD = Line(Point(C), Point(D))\nline_EF = Line(Point(E), Point(F))\n\nP_AB_CD = line_AB.intersection(line_CD)[0]\nP_CD_EF = line_CD.intersection(line_EF)[0]\nP_EF_AB = line_EF.intersection(line_AB)[0]\nP_AB_CD, P_CD_EF, P_EF_AB\n\n```output\n[Block 1/1] FAILED\n  Error: Traceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages/sympy/__init__.py\", line 22, in <module>\n    import mpmath\n  File \"/tmp/tmphu2_2bog.py\", line 22, in _safe_import\n    return _original_import(name, *args, **kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages/mpmath/__init__.py\", line 5, in <module>\n    from .ctx_fp import FPContext\n  File \"/tmp/tmphu2_2bog.py\", line 22, in _safe_import\n    return _original_import(name, *args, **kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages/mpmath/ctx_fp.py\", line 1, in <module>\n    from .ctx_base import StandardBaseContext\n  File \"/tmp/tmphu2_2bog.py\", line 22, in _safe_import\n    return _original_import(name, *args, **kwargs)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-pac